Package rrhvella.coursework1

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Chord
    The harmonic information occupying a span of time.
    ChordProfiles
    For each scale, ChordProfiles associates a chord for a note at a given offset from the scale's tonic.
    ConsonanceProfiles
    For each scale, ConsonanceProfiles associates an interval from the tonic with a consonance factor.
    ContextSensitiveNonDeterministicLSystem
    Specifies a context-sensitive stochastic L-system.
    ContextSensitiveNonDeterministicPredecessor
    A predecessor of a production in a context-sensitive stochastic L-system.
    MelodyGenerator
    Generates a melody using a context-sensitive stochastic L-system.
    StructuredPolyphonicLSystemNotator
    Generates a MIDI sequence based on the outputs of context-sensitive stochastic L-systems.
    StructuredPolyphonicLSystemNotator.TokenAnalysis
    Analyses the structure string, and uses the other information provided by the user to generate and organise the tokens for this piece.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ChordType
    Specifies the classification for a chord, as well as the interval pattern associated with that classification.
    Note
    An abstract description of a frequency in Western music.
    Scale
    The harmonic information associated with a classical Western scale.
